<SLUG> BC-OLY-NOTEBOOK-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SQUEEZE IS ON SYDNEY 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By JOHN POWERS  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOSTON _ Though the Sydney organizers insist there's room for
only 10,200 athletes under their big tent, the Lords of the Rings
keep coming up with new sports and events for the 2000 Olympic
program.
</P>
<P>
   Besides tacking on triathlon, taekwondo, trampoline, tumbling,
and women's water polo, the International Olympic Committee has
added the women's pole vault and hammer throw plus two wheelchair
events to track and field. To keep from having athletes camp in the
hallways, the IOC is reducing entries in sports such as boxing.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, Salt Lake City, which already has 70 medal events
with the inclusion of pursuit events in biathlon and an expanded
field (from six to eight) for women's ice hockey, may put on the
brakes. Odds are it won't add skeleton sledding and women's ski
jumping; women's bobsledding is still under discussion.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Superb showing by the US rowers, who won nine medals at the
recent world regatta in Cologne and barely missed topping the
table. Most impressive performance was by the men's eight, which
came out of fifth place to become the first US big boat to retain a
global crown and the first in seven years (since Germany) to
repeat. The women's lightweight double of Worcester's  &UR; Christine
Collins  &LR; and  &UR; Sarah Garner  &LR; also claimed a gold, with silvers
coming from the women's eight (with East Bridgewater's  &UR; Wendy
Wilbur  &LR; aboard), the men's lightweight eight, and the women's
lightweight quad (with Cambridge's  &UR; Terry Paige &LR; ), and bronzes from
the men's coxed pair and lightweight quad and women's pair and
lightweight pair. With a bit of luck, the Yanks could have had a
couple more medals. But the pair of  &UR; Adam Holland  &LR; and
Newburyport's  &UR; Cy Beasley  &LR; missed a bronze by .03 seconds and
sculler  &UR; Jamie Koven &LR; , the defending world champ, popped his
oarlock in the semis and missed making the final. As expected, the
host Germans (10 medals) led the standings. Great Britain's
legendary  &UR; Steven Redgrave  &LR; won a record eighth world title in the
uncoxed four, and Canada's  &UR; Marnie McBean  &LR; made history by winning
a global medal (a silver in the four) in her sixth different event
... No excuses from  &UR; Marion Jones  &LR; after she'd lost the World Cup
long jump to Germany's  &UR; Heike Drechsler  &LR; in Johannesburg's cold
rain last Sunday for her only defeat of the year. ``It's the same
for all of us,'' Jones said. ``It's not as if it got cold just for
me.'' Jones still won the 100 and 200 to lead the US women to the
team title after pocketing nearly $700,000 in bonuses at the
previous weekend's Grand Prix final in Moscow. Word now is that the
international federation will rejigger the schedule for next year's
world outdoor meet to let Jones try for gold in both the 100 and
long jump, whose qualifying rounds now conflict ... Could be the
end of the line for Olympic sprint champion  &UR; Donovan Bailey &LR; , &UR;  &LR; who
ruptured his Achilles' tendon last week in a pickup basketball game
in Toronto. Ironically, Bailey walked away from a car wreck last
year with only a sore neck ... Yes, that is China's  &UR; Wang Junxia
 &LR; jogging around the Colorado State campus this fall. The Olympic
distance champion is paying her own way as a student. No word on
whether she'll be doing any cross-country for the Golden Ram
varsity.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Though the International Skating Union vows it won't open the
Olympics to all figure skaters, it's clearly heading in that
direction with its new Grand Slam, which has most of the top
eligibles and ineligibles going head-to-head in front of ISU
judges. Next weekend's inaugural in Charleston, S.C., features the
last three men's Olympic gold medalists ( &UR; Ilia Kulik &LR; , &UR; Alexei
Urmanov &LR; , &UR; Viktor Petrenko &LR; ) &UR;  &LR; and world champions  &UR; Alexei
Yagudin &LR; , &UR; Kurt Browning &LR; , &UR;  &LR; and  &UR; Todd Eldredge &LR; , &UR;  &LR; plus women's world
titlists  &UR; Michelle Kwan &LR; , &UR; Chen Lu &LR; , &UR;  &LR; and  &UR; Yuka Sato &LR; . Winners
receive $40,000. Though Kwan has her high school diploma in hand
(from Rim of the World HS in Lake Arrowhead, Calif.), she's putting
college on hold until next fall while she continues to focus on
skating ... As expected, the ISU has raised the bar for male
skaters in the short program, allowing a quadruple jump. Though the
quad is optional, it'll soon become all but compulsory for anyone
who wants a medal. The ISU has also made a throw jump (double or
triple) one of the required elements for pairs ... Terrific field
for next month's Evening With Champions benefit at Harvard's Bright
Center: Yagudin,  &UR; Oksana Baiul &LR; , &UR; Paul Wylie &LR; , &UR;  &LR; world pairs champs
 &UR; Elena Berezhnaya  &LR; and  &UR; Anton Sikharulidze &LR; , &UR;  &LR; and the new dance
combo of Olympic champ  &UR; Evgeny Platov  &LR; and former medalist  &UR; Maya
Usova &LR; . Dates are Oct. 23-24-25; call 617-493-8172 for details ...
New coach for the Russian hockey team is the legendary  &UR; Alexander
Yakushev &LR; , &UR;  &LR; who won two Olympic gold medals with the Big Red
Machine and also played in the historic 1972 showdown with Team
Canada ... How does the international soccer federation plan to
raise the level of the Olympic tournament? By raising the number of
over-23 players on each team from three to five and massaging the
European club schedule to make better players available. Though the
IOC would love to have the best playing the best, as it now does in
basketball and hockey, FIFA doesn't want to diminish the importance
of the quadrennial World Cup ... Lots of new faces on US
Speedskating's coaching staff for the next quadrennium.  &UR; Dan
Immerfall &LR; , &UR;  &LR; a three-time Olympian and 1976 bronze medalist, will
be overall technical coordinator.  &UR; Finn Halvorsen  &LR; will direct the
long track program, with  &UR; Bart Schouten  &LR; handling all-arounders and
 &UR; Dave Besteman  &LR; sprinters.  &UR; Pat Wentland  &LR; will coach the short
trackers.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &UR;  &LR;   &UR;  &LR; Improved showing for the US freestyle wrestlers, who finished
third at the recent world championships in Tehran after placing
sixth last year.  &UR; Sam Henson  &LR; won the gold medal at 119 pounds, and
 &UR; Cary Kolat  &LR; (138) and  &UR; Lincoln McIlravy  &LR; (152) each took bronzes.
The host Iranians won the team title ahead of the Russians ...
Since it's not known when the Olympic qualifying tournament will be
(it determines whether pros will be available), USA Baseball has
scrubbed this autumn's tryouts for next year's national team. The
federation still will choose an all-collegian squad next year for
international games _ just in case ... If you have Greek
grandparents and you can hit the breaking ball, you can make it to
Olympus. Since Athens is hosting the 2004 Summer Games, Greece has
automatically qualified for the baseball draw. Problem is, the
Greeks have no team and only one diamond in the entire country. So
they're looking for Americans of Greek extraction. Where have you
gone,  &UR; Harry Agganis &LR; ?
</P>
</TEXT>
