   GERMANY-POLITICS (Hanover) _ If Gerhard Schroeder has tried to
communicate anything during his long quest to unseat Chancellor
Helmut Kohl, it is that he is worldly and modern. But with
elections just one week away, Schroeder's past is coming back to
haunt him. By Edmund L. Andrews.
</P>
