the past two years, it has seen its Nielsen ratings plummet, losing
more than 25 percent of its viewers. The drop hurt ABC's prestige,
but the financial pain is far worse. The downturn at ``Good Morning
America'' came almost directly from efforts to improve it, by
making it newsier and more sophisticated, in keeping with changing
American habits and interests. A look at a show in trouble. By
Lawrie Mifflin.
