</P>
<P>
   MEDSCHOOL-ELDERLY (Baltimore) _ A new approach to geriatrics at
Johns Hopkins Medical School has students making house calls and
taking the time to get to know patients. It is far from the high
technology approach to patients usually emphasized in modern
medical training; yet it is a part of what is regarded as the
cutting edge training in geriatrics that is required of all
residents in internal medicine at Hopkins. By Sara Rimer.
</P>
<P>
   AMERINDIAN-TOURISM (Umatilla Reservation, Ore.) _ American
Indian reservations, long considered economic deserts amidst a
landscape of general prosperity, are finding that they have a lot
more to offer the world than casinos and art galleries _ they have
their homes, their backyards, their stories. Visitors, especially a
growing number of Europeans, are traveling to some of the country's
most remote places, like this Indian reservation in central Oregon,
in search of life many Americans overlook on their vacations. By
Timothy Egan.
</P>
