clusters simply don't exist; that there is a lot of cancer
everywhere and neighborhood concentrations of the disease result
from chance, not the environment. But people who live in areas
where the incidence of cancer is higher than expected have rarely
been content with that rationale. By Susan Sachs.
</P>
