<HEADLINE>
TREASURY, BOND OFFERINGS SET FOR THIS WEEK 
</HEADLINE>
  (th) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Treasury's schedule of financings this week comprises
Monday's regular weekly auction of new three- and six-month bills
and a two-year note being auctioned Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   According to traders, at the close of the New York cash market
on Friday the rate on the outstanding three-month bill was at 4.48
percent and the rate on the six-month issue at 4.61 percent. In
when-issued trading the two-year note was offered at a price to
yield 4.57 percent.
</P>
<P>
   The following taxable and tax-exempt fixed-income issues are
scheduled for pricing this week:
</P>
<P>
   TAX EXEMPT
</P>
<P>
   MONDAY
</P>
<P>
   Colorado Springs, $95 million of revenue bonds. Competitive.
</P>
<P>
   TUESDAY
</P>
<P>
   Alpine School District, Utah, $69 million of general obligation
bonds. Competitive.
</P>
<P>
   Pittsburgh, $132.5 million of debt securities. Competitive.
</P>
<P>
   WEDNESDAY
</P>
<P>
   Mississippi, $57.7 million of general obligation bonds.
Competitive.
</P>
<P>
   Nevada, $55 million of general obligation bonds for university
system project. Competitive.
</P>
<P>
   THURSDAY
</P>
<P>
   Portland, Ore., $160 million of revenue bonds. Competitive.
</P>
<P>
   TAX EXEMPT
</P>
<P>
   ONE DAY DURING THE WEEK
</P>
<P>
   Chesapeake Bridge and Tunnel Authority, $50 million of debt
securities. Paine Webber Inc.
</P>
<P>
   Connecticut Light and Power, Connecticut Development Authority,
$415 million of debt securities. Morgan Stanley Dean Witter.
</P>
<P>
   Dormitory Authority of the State of New York, $142.5 million of
revenue bonds for St. John's University. Morgan Stanley Dean
Witter.
</P>
<P>
   Miramar, Fla., $50 million of water and wastewater revenue
bonds. Salomon Smith Barney.
</P>
<P>
   Missouri Health and Education Facility, $225 million of debt
securities for BJC Health System. J.P. Morgan Securities.
</P>
<P>
   Nebraska Investment Finance Authority, $70 million of debt
securities. Lehman Brothers.
</P>
<P>
   North Carolina Medical Care, $200 million of debt securities for
Duke University health system. Salomon Smith Barney.
</P>
<P>
   Ohio, $250 million of turnpike revenue bonds. Merrill Lynch &AMP;
Co.
</P>
<P>
   Spokane, Wash., $73 million of refunding bonds for regional
solid waste management systems. Goldman, Sachs &AMP; Co.
</P>
<P>
   Tennessee School Bond Authority, $83.5 million of second program
bonds and refunding bonds for higher-education facility. A.G.
Edwards &AMP; Sons. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
