<HEADLINE>
FUMBLES FORGOTTEN 
</HEADLINE>
  (lh) 
 By MIKE FREEMAN   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. _ Sunday began as a nightmare for New York
Jets running back Curtis Martin. In the beginning of the Jets' 44-6
victory over Indianapolis, the Jets were on their own 25-yard line.
Seconds after getting the handoff, Martin fumbled when safety Jason
Belser poked the ball loose. Luckily, quarterback Vinny Testaverde
pounced on it.
</P>
<P>
   On the very next series, Martin fumbled again. This time, guard
Todd Burger recovered. As Martin walked to the sideline after the
second fumble, one thought raced through his head.
</P>
<P>
   ``I said to myself, `God, I'm not going to panic, but I need
your help right now,''' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Martin, however, is the kind of player who can make two bad
plays but then, on the next 10, show the kind of explosion and
game-breaking ability that few running backs have. By the time his
day was over, those two fumbles were forgotten. He finished with
144 yards rushing on 23 carries.
</P>
<P>
   All of the Jets' backs had a good day. Fullback Jerald Sowell
had eight carries for 82 yards, and Leon Johnson had eight for 52
yards.
</P>
<P>
   The Jets' backs even caught the ball well. Martin, Johnson and
Keith Byars combined for four catches for 141 yards and one
touchdown. Byars' catch, his 587th, tied him with Marcus Allen for
most career catches by a back.
</P>
<P>
   Chrebet Sprains Ankle
</P>
<P>
   The only bad news for the Jets was that wide receiver Wayne
Chrebet sprained his left ankle after making a catch early in the
third quarter. After the game, Chrebet had a cast placed on the
ankle as a precaution.
</P>
<P>
   ``We thought it might be worse,'' Jets Coach Bill Parcells said.
``It wasn't, thank goodness.''
</P>
<P>
   Chrebet's 11-yard catch at the end of the first quarter gave him
221 for his career, placing him 10th on the Jets' list.
</P>
<P>
   It's Up, It's No Good
</P>
<P>
   Kicker John Hall had an extra point blocked, ending his streak
of 43 straight attempts without a miss.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-09-20-98 2324EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
